01:40:12.010 --> 01:40:18.420
As a writer and artist, I always
am so interested in the ways

01:40:18.420 --> 01:40:22.660
that we use language
very specifically, very

01:40:22.660 --> 01:40:26.080
strategically, in order to
make certain kinds of points.

01:40:26.080 --> 01:40:27.710
And on the other
hand, whenever anybody

01:40:27.710 --> 01:40:30.850
starts talking about gendered
nouns in romance languages,

01:40:30.850 --> 01:40:33.620
I can't help but think
about things like in French,

01:40:33.620 --> 01:40:36.490
"mustache" is a feminine
noun and "vagina"

01:40:36.490 --> 01:40:41.840
is a masculine,
which it possibly

01:40:41.840 --> 01:40:46.570
