01:54:31.790 --> 01:54:35.290
have to talk about gender.

01:54:35.290 --> 01:54:39.516
Why is it not possible
to-- all right.

01:54:39.516 --> 01:54:42.290
Let me back up a step.

01:54:42.290 --> 01:54:44.080
I think that it
should be possible,

01:54:44.080 --> 01:54:49.340
and it seems like it is, to
have gender nonspecific language

01:54:49.340 --> 01:54:53.870
that can be used both when
gender is not a factor

01:54:53.870 --> 01:54:57.350
or we are signaling that we
don't want it to be a factor

01:54:57.350 --> 01:55:08.800
and for situations when a person
does not identify themselves

01:55:08.800 --> 01:55:13.480
with any of the most
common gender categories.

01:55:13.480 --> 01:55:17.050
I think that the
interesting piece for me

01:55:17.050 --> 01:55:20.950
starts to crop up because as
soon as you make a list of all

01:55:20.950 --> 01:55:24.580
the possibilities-- I
was a little bit involved

01:55:24.580 --> 01:55:27.760
with the folks who made 51
genders on Facebook or 52

01:55:27.760 --> 01:55:29.760
genders on Facebook
or whatever it is.

01:55:29.760 --> 01:55:33.070
And as soon as they released
the list and your Facebook

01:55:33.070 --> 01:55:36.190
had a dropdown
box of 52 options,

01:55:36.190 --> 01:55:38.300
people immediately
started to complain

01:55:38.300 --> 01:55:43.500
that their particular
preferred gender wasn't listed.

01:55:43.500 --> 01:55:46.260
And that is the thing that
crops up over and over again.

01:55:46.260 --> 01:55:49.850
At a certain moment in identity
politics people start to say,

01:55:49.850 --> 01:55:54.490
but I prefer to identify myself
as this complicated, 11-word

01:55:54.490 --> 01:55:58.160
adjectival phrase, and I
don't see that recognized

01:55:58.160 --> 01:55:59.580
in the literature.

01:55:59.580 --> 01:56:03.110
And at the same time,
we all, I think,

01:56:03.110 --> 01:56:08.470
recognize that there is value
to having some ability to label

01:56:08.470 --> 01:56:12.540
ourselves because it gives
us a banner to group under,

01:56:12.540 --> 01:56:15.678
for certain topics.

01:56:15.678 --> 01:56:17.470
-[INAUDIBLE] Yeah.

01:56:17.470 --> 01:56:20.790
-I'll just acknowledge there's
a fundamental value question

01:56:20.790 --> 01:56:23.270
at the base of the debate.

01:56:23.270 --> 01:56:27.480
I tend to be on the side
of a more gender neutral,

01:56:27.480 --> 01:56:30.240
minimize the salience
of gender as a category,

01:56:30.240 --> 01:56:31.980
but I totally
recognize there are

01:56:31.980 --> 01:56:35.490
people who argue that gender
is incredibly valuable.

01:56:35.490 --> 01:56:37.870
I want to say I'm a woman
and I identify as a woman

01:56:37.870 --> 01:56:40.380
and I want to have spaces
where there's women.

01:56:40.380 --> 01:56:42.490
And then you might
argue well, and we

01:56:42.490 --> 01:56:44.280
need 12 different
genders, but we

01:56:44.280 --> 01:56:47.080
want to maintain
all these genders

01:56:47.080 --> 01:56:49.340
and the focus and the salience.

01:56:49.340 --> 01:56:52.360
And I think that's a
fundamental mental debate

01:56:52.360 --> 01:56:55.210
that science isn't
necessarily going to solve.

01:56:55.210 --> 01:56:56.210
-OK.

01:56:56.210 --> 01:56:58.530
Last word?

01:56:58.530 --> 01:57:02.100
-I'm not in that
conversation yet.

01:57:02.100 --> 01:57:04.400
I'm still in my own
tribal [? mind ?]

01:57:04.400 --> 01:57:08.990
of how I'm constructing gender,
but I will be coming to Bear

01:57:08.990 --> 01:57:12.240
and get some information
from him about everything

01:57:12.240 --> 01:57:13.950
else in the Western culture.

01:57:13.950 --> 01:57:16.810
So that's something that's
still not there yet.

01:57:16.810 --> 01:57:17.458
-Thank you.

